The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Holding sympathy for pacers

New Delhi: Former West Indies fast 

 bowler Michael Holding says cricket is more about skill 

 than strength and if a fast bowler was resorting to drugs 

 it was only to strengthen his body to keep up with the demands 

 of the modern day game. 

Personally, I believe there is too much pressure on modern-day players and especially on the fast bowlers only Brett Lee manages to stay fit for any length of time, while Shoaib has missed as many Tests as he has played, Holding said on a website. 

 In my playing days, I never heard of any fast 

 bowler ever taking steroids. But these days they have to 

 constantly worry ... 




